-> rrel_example:
[ black and white films are films that have been made without the use of a color palette. Instead, they use shades of gray, white, and black to create an image. Black and white films were common in cinema until the advent of color films in the middle of the last century. However, even after that, many directors continued to use the black and white palette to create the effect of the old time or to enhance the emotional power of the film. Today, black and white films are rarely made, but some modern films still use this style to create a special atmosphere.]
